Leading deal origination and execution including sourcing, valuation, and negotiation of investment projects across major sectors in Japan and/or Asia; 
Clearly present investment opportunities to leadership teams by identifying and discussing key drivers of value, and conducting necessary research to verify investment hypotheses;
Leading research into potential new areas of investment, and formulating new strategies for investment areas, including market sizing, surveys, interviews, and extensive data analysis;
Partner with deal teams, internal leaders and Business Groups to formulate investment strategies and post-deal management strategies; including working with cross functional teams to manage deal processes, finance monitoring, business analysis, business cooperation, valuation adjustments, supporting Board meetings, and handling related documentation; 
Experience working with and coordinating external advisors including investment banks, financial advisors, commercial due diligence, consultants, and other professional service providers;
Maintain a strong network of quality relationship across wide ecosystem of founders, investors, colleagues and other stakeholders;
Comfortable handling a large volume of work, with a positive attitude, in a matrixed organization;
Native spoken and written Japanese language ability, in addition to near-native fluency in English and/or Mandarin Chinese.

